WEBVTT

00:03.233 --> 00:05.167
Lookey here. Wow-wee.

00:06.733 --> 00:08.667
Ike, you're a hell of
a piano man.

00:08.733 --> 00:11.600
But I ain't gonna jive you.
You can't sing for crap.

00:13.067 --> 00:15.467
I dream of making
music like that someday.

00:15.533 --> 00:16.600
Leonard Chess?

00:16.667 --> 00:18.100
Yeah. I'm Leonard Chess.
Who are you?

00:18.167 --> 00:20.233
It doesn't matter who I am,
it matters what I got.

00:20.300 --> 00:21.833
This is a cash business.

00:21.900 --> 00:25.033
Based on trust and our mutual
desire to make you a star.

00:25.100 --> 00:26.367
Can I trust you, Hank?

00:26.433 --> 00:29.333
-Damn straight.
Okay.

00:34.000 --> 00:35.467
Well, that's not good.

00:35.533 --> 00:37.600
Call immediately
if you hear from him.

00:38.333 --> 00:40.233
What did he say?

00:42.400 --> 00:43.733
Sam never showed.

00:45.300 --> 00:47.367
Dewey figured he went on home.

00:47.433 --> 00:49.367
Let's try the hospital again.

00:49.433 --> 00:53.700
♪ How much is that doggy
in the window

00:53.767 --> 00:55.200
Lucas,
you best roll up that hose

00:55.267 --> 00:56.567
before your bus gets here.

00:56.633 --> 01:00.867
♪ The one with the waggly tail

01:00.933 --> 01:05.733
♪ How much is that doggy
in the window

01:06.967 --> 01:12.267
♪ I do hope
that doggy is for sale

01:12.333 --> 01:17.067
♪ I read in the papers
there are robbers

01:18.433 --> 01:23.533
♪ With flashlights
that shine in the dark

01:23.600 --> 01:29.233
♪ My love needs a doggy
to protect him

01:29.300 --> 01:34.367
♪ And scare them away
with one bark

01:35.667 --> 01:39.800
♪ I don't want a bunny
or a kitty

01:41.667 --> 01:42.700
Morning.

01:43.867 --> 01:46.467
Mom, there's a man
in my swing set!

01:46.533 --> 01:50.900
♪ I don't want a bowl
of little fishies ♪

02:29.167 --> 02:30.633
Morning, Nadine.

02:30.700 --> 02:33.067
Are you all right, Sam?

02:33.067 --> 02:35.067
-Never better.

02:38.433 --> 02:39.967
Here you go.

02:41.133 --> 02:44.367
What kind of life
is this, Marion?

02:44.433 --> 02:45.800
I mean...

02:46.600 --> 02:50.200
Me and Sam, we're broke.

02:50.267 --> 02:52.967
I don't have
much of a husband,

02:53.067 --> 02:55.400
Knox doesn't have
much of a father.

02:57.367 --> 02:58.667
I know why I'm doing this.

02:58.733 --> 03:01.567
I just can't really understand
why you are.

03:03.367 --> 03:04.600
Sam?

03:05.400 --> 03:07.167
Oh, dear Lord.

03:08.500 --> 03:10.133
Are you all right?

03:11.267 --> 03:14.067
What in the world happened?

03:15.667 --> 03:20.533
Well, uh, I tried taking
a shortcut on the way home.

03:20.600 --> 03:23.167
It didn't go so well.

03:33.167 --> 03:35.100
I've got to get Knox
up for school, so...

03:38.667 --> 03:41.300
I sure could use
a cup of joe myself.

04:00.333 --> 04:01.700
Oh, Jimmy.

04:01.767 --> 04:03.067
I surely don't believe

04:03.067 --> 04:05.533
life will ever be
the same again, cuz.

04:06.967 --> 04:11.167
Oh, we need to avert
our eyes from this, Jerry Lee.

04:11.233 --> 04:14.200
So you've been saying for
the past couple of hours now.

04:14.267 --> 04:17.067
Only your eyes seem to have
a mind of their own now,

04:17.133 --> 04:18.500
don't they?

04:19.300 --> 04:20.533
-Whoo!
-Oh.

04:20.600 --> 04:22.633
I wonder if Peggy
looks like that.

04:22.700 --> 04:25.100
Don't you dare
talk about my girl like that.

04:25.167 --> 04:26.833
Huh? Your girl?

04:26.900 --> 04:28.400
Pretty sure it was me
she was eyeing

04:28.467 --> 04:31.500
after I dazzled her with my
exquisite ivory tickling.

04:31.567 --> 04:33.067
Only look that angel
was giving you

04:33.067 --> 04:35.400
was one of pity
for your unsalvaged soul.

04:35.467 --> 04:36.867
Well, why don't we
let Peggy decide

04:36.933 --> 04:39.133
who's right in this little
difference of opinion?

04:39.200 --> 04:40.600
Huh?

04:40.667 --> 04:42.800
Jerry Lee,
Jimmy, I need a lil' help!

04:42.867 --> 04:45.200
Okay, Momma.

04:46.733 --> 04:49.067
Fine.
May the best man win.

04:49.067 --> 04:50.867
Well, suits me, cuz,
'cause you know what?

04:50.933 --> 04:52.167
I always do.

04:52.233 --> 04:53.233
Ow.

05:02.633 --> 05:05.700
Hey, sugar,
got some more for you.

05:05.767 --> 05:08.800
Oh, you are a godsend.

05:08.867 --> 05:10.967
We sure can use the work.

05:12.500 --> 05:14.733
-Is everything okay?

05:15.900 --> 05:19.533
Uh, fine, fine. How're you?

05:20.167 --> 05:21.633
How's Sam?

05:21.700 --> 05:23.467
This morning, he looked like
something the cat dragged in

05:23.533 --> 05:24.967
and the goat wouldn't eat.

05:25.067 --> 05:28.133
Just a little mishap.

05:28.200 --> 05:29.667
Now, Becky...

05:29.733 --> 05:32.233
I'm not one to gossip.

05:32.300 --> 05:34.067
But, I'm just saying

05:34.067 --> 05:37.700
the paperboy told Gladys Twain
from down the street

05:39.067 --> 05:41.933
that he saw Sam
take his trousers off outside

05:42.067 --> 05:44.067
for God and country to see.

05:44.133 --> 05:46.867
And she told the widower
Mr. Petty down at the garage

05:46.933 --> 05:49.067
who told Betsy who can't
keep her mouth shut...

05:52.900 --> 05:54.067
Sam!

05:55.533 --> 05:57.600
Sorry.

05:57.667 --> 06:00.067
Always a pleasure
to see you, Nadine.

06:11.600 --> 06:14.167
Bless your heart, dear.

06:26.567 --> 06:27.900
Where are you off to?

06:28.867 --> 06:30.267
Got a session.

06:34.700 --> 06:35.967
What?

06:37.200 --> 06:39.967
Well, it's just 5:00
in the afternoon,

06:40.067 --> 06:43.167
and my husband, who's now
the talk of the town,

06:43.233 --> 06:47.500
just woke up
having been out all night

06:47.567 --> 06:49.800
without letting me know
where he was.

06:49.867 --> 06:53.367
And after smashing
the family car,

06:53.433 --> 06:58.167
he just walks around
like it's all la-di-da,

06:58.233 --> 07:00.433
and then asks, "What?"

07:03.733 --> 07:05.267
You know what, Becks,

07:05.333 --> 07:08.300
I'm jammed up all day long
with sessions.

07:08.367 --> 07:12.167
Night time's the only time
I got to find new acts.

07:12.900 --> 07:14.233
I gotta go.

07:14.300 --> 07:15.433
Sam...

07:16.767 --> 07:18.067
I thought we came here

07:18.067 --> 07:21.067
to build a stable
recording business.

07:21.067 --> 07:23.467
Commercials, testimonials,
recitals...

07:23.533 --> 07:25.800
And if you haven't noticed,

07:25.867 --> 07:30.867
you've taken in half
the neighborhood's sewing,

07:30.933 --> 07:33.700
'cause the recording part
ain't cutting it.

07:35.167 --> 07:38.500
I... I thought Rocket 88
was the big hit we needed?

07:38.567 --> 07:40.600
Huh. Yeah.

07:40.667 --> 07:42.267
Turns out that drunk Brenston

07:42.333 --> 07:45.200
ain't nothing but
a damned one-hit wonder.

07:45.267 --> 07:48.700
Look, I can't pay today's
bills on yesterday's hits.

07:48.767 --> 07:50.167
Sam.

07:52.900 --> 07:55.200
I'm worried about you.

07:55.267 --> 07:57.500
I made an appointment
with a new doctor,

07:57.567 --> 07:59.367
and I think that we...

08:02.633 --> 08:04.767
Thanks for consulting me.

08:05.833 --> 08:08.167
You're my wife, Becky.

08:08.233 --> 08:10.267
Stop acting like
my damn mother!

08:10.333 --> 08:13.867
Well, you stop acting
like a damn child!

08:19.933 --> 08:21.367
Well, I don't need this.

08:21.433 --> 08:22.767
I've got work to do!

08:27.067 --> 08:31.433
Two Japs, out of ammo,
rushed me with bayonets.

08:31.500 --> 08:32.767
Time I was done,

08:32.833 --> 08:34.167
you couldn't have
matched up the pieces

08:34.233 --> 08:36.233
to tell "chop" from "suey"
if they paid you.

08:36.300 --> 08:39.567
Uh, Mr. Dean, sir,
may I please have a word?

08:39.633 --> 08:41.067
Get out of here, boy.

08:41.067 --> 08:43.933
You don't have a thing to say
I wanna hear.

08:45.267 --> 08:47.433
-Sir?
-I'll be back.

08:47.500 --> 08:50.167
You just cost me a sale.
What do you want?

08:50.233 --> 08:52.567
To apologize.

08:52.633 --> 08:54.500
Look, I'm sorry
if I did anything

08:54.567 --> 08:56.767
to disrespect you
or your family.

08:56.833 --> 09:00.500
-That wasn't my intention.
-What was your intention?

09:00.567 --> 09:02.933
-I just like the music is all.

09:03.067 --> 09:06.667
You don't drink from colored
water fountains, do you, boy?

09:07.400 --> 09:09.533
Well, no, sir.

09:09.600 --> 09:10.967
Well, you see my point?

09:13.400 --> 09:15.333
You may be kissing my daughter

09:15.400 --> 09:17.833
with those lips of yours
someday.

09:19.300 --> 09:21.333
It won't happen again, sir.

09:21.400 --> 09:23.433
I care deeply about Trixie.

09:23.500 --> 09:25.633
I'd never do anything
to harm her.

09:27.567 --> 09:29.900
-I believe you.

09:29.967 --> 09:31.967
And hell, boy,

09:32.067 --> 09:35.233
can't have you climbing up
my house every night.

09:35.300 --> 09:36.500
You'll ruin the siding.

09:37.267 --> 09:38.500
Get!

09:56.767 --> 09:58.367
Hey, Trixie from Dixie.

09:58.433 --> 10:00.067
Hey, you know,
I talked to your daddy.

10:00.067 --> 10:01.133
That so?

10:01.200 --> 10:02.467
Oh, honey,
everything is hunky dory.

10:02.533 --> 10:03.633
And?

10:03.700 --> 10:06.933
-Well, he forgave me.
-Did he?

10:07.000 --> 10:09.900
Well, maybe you two
should go steady. Hmm.

10:14.500 --> 10:16.233
Stop pestering her.

10:24.200 --> 10:26.733
I tell you, Beau, this better
be one hell of a bar.

10:26.800 --> 10:31.167
Johnny boy, this ain't just
any old bar. Come on.

11:01.300 --> 11:02.733
Uh...

11:07.733 --> 11:10.300
Why you here?

11:10.367 --> 11:11.700
This Russian sector!

11:11.767 --> 11:13.267
What the hell is he saying?

11:13.333 --> 11:16.300
Well, I think he's saying
we're in the Russian sector.

11:16.367 --> 11:19.100
-Well, we know that.
-We do?

11:19.167 --> 11:21.600
Soon, all Russia.

11:21.667 --> 11:24.667
All world Russian sector!

11:26.233 --> 11:28.100
Hey, y'all would be
goose-steppin' to Sieg Heil

11:28.167 --> 11:30.167
if America hadn't come
to save your sorry asses.

11:31.767 --> 11:34.067
Well, lookie
what we have here.

11:35.300 --> 11:38.333
Can't you read a map?
Italy's that way.

11:38.400 --> 11:41.200
We got the commies,
and we got the hillbillies.

11:42.667 --> 11:44.167
They're telling us
they gonna rule the world.

11:44.233 --> 11:45.233
Is that so?

11:46.233 --> 11:47.233
Da.

11:48.433 --> 11:49.900
Hell of a choice.

11:49.967 --> 11:53.133
On one hand, we have sorry
excuses for American GIs.

11:53.200 --> 11:54.233
And on the other...

12:11.733 --> 12:13.833
Guys, let's get
the hell out of here!

12:13.900 --> 12:16.100
Hey, you left this vodka!

12:24.567 --> 12:26.533
No wonder these Russkies
are miserable bastards.

12:26.600 --> 12:28.167
Their damn booze
is made out of potatoes.

12:28.233 --> 12:30.100
Oh, man, who cares if
it's made out of dirty socks,

12:30.167 --> 12:31.633
sure does the job.

12:31.700 --> 12:33.200
What do you expect
from a hick who drinks whiskey

12:33.267 --> 12:34.300
made from corn?

12:34.367 --> 12:35.400
Well, that ain't whiskey,

12:35.467 --> 12:37.900
that'd be, uh, corn liquor.

12:40.167 --> 12:41.600
Fraeulein.

12:42.267 --> 12:44.067
Paesanos!

12:44.067 --> 12:46.567
-What do you mean, paesanos?
-It means stand-up guys.

12:46.633 --> 12:47.833
Oh.

12:47.900 --> 12:49.533
But we're all
stand-up guys tonight.

12:49.600 --> 12:50.967
Party time, boys.

12:51.067 --> 12:52.900
I... I got me a girl
waiting back home.

12:52.967 --> 12:55.067
She got Sam Spade
keeping tabs on you?

12:55.100 --> 12:57.167
Who?
Maltese Falcon?

12:57.233 --> 12:58.333
Bogie?

12:58.400 --> 13:00.367
Man, even I know
Bogie and Bacall.

13:00.433 --> 13:02.700
Guess you are
just a rube after all.

13:02.767 --> 13:06.200
You sneak into East Germany
just so you can window watch?

13:11.400 --> 13:12.700
How you doing?

13:12.767 --> 13:14.067
I don't know what you're
saying, but I like it.

13:16.067 --> 13:18.133
Uh... Uh, no, thank...

13:18.200 --> 13:19.533
Um...

13:21.933 --> 13:24.167
"No, thank you"?

13:24.233 --> 13:27.300
Uh, I spent all my money
on my guitars, so I...

13:27.367 --> 13:29.067
Uh, yeah, yeah, yeah,
I'll pay for it.

13:29.067 --> 13:30.333
Besides, I don't...
Danke schoen.

13:30.400 --> 13:32.500
I don't really feel like it,
that's all.

13:32.567 --> 13:35.167
Ah, you never did it.

13:35.233 --> 13:36.767
He never did it.

13:36.833 --> 13:38.067
Guys, he never did it.

13:38.100 --> 13:39.267
I done it plenty of times.

13:39.333 --> 13:40.700
You never did it.
He never did...

13:40.767 --> 13:41.767
No...

13:44.067 --> 13:45.233
Man, you didn't tell me that.

13:48.500 --> 13:50.300
Jungfrau? Jungfrau?

13:50.367 --> 13:51.467
Jungfrau!

13:51.533 --> 13:53.500
Jungfrau! Jungfrau!

13:53.567 --> 13:57.900
Jungfrau! Jungfrau!
Jungfrau! Jungfrau!

13:57.967 --> 13:59.733
That's all that's left.

14:03.367 --> 14:05.333
Yeah!

14:06.800 --> 14:08.133
Make us proud.

14:16.100 --> 14:19.300
♪ And I still
wouldn't let her go

14:19.367 --> 14:22.367
♪ A train kept a-rollin'
all night long

14:22.433 --> 14:23.633
Hey, Trix.

14:23.700 --> 14:26.167
♪ A train kept a-rollin'
all night long

14:26.233 --> 14:29.167
♪ A train kept a-rollin'
all night long

14:29.233 --> 14:32.267
♪ A train kept a-rollin'
all night long

14:32.333 --> 14:35.233
♪ A train kept a-rollin'
all night long

14:35.300 --> 14:39.300
♪ And I still
wouldn't let her go ♪

14:44.933 --> 14:46.367
-I had me

14:46.433 --> 14:49.433
a similar situation
with Betty Caldwell last year.

14:50.967 --> 14:53.133
Every time
I tried to talk to her,

14:53.200 --> 14:55.633
damn girlfriends
pulled her away.

14:55.700 --> 14:56.867
What'd you do?

14:56.933 --> 14:59.667
Disguised myself
with a big old Stetson

14:59.733 --> 15:03.433
and followed her one night
after Billy Bean's party.

15:03.500 --> 15:05.233
How'd that turn out?

15:05.300 --> 15:08.233
Guess I kind of startled her.

15:08.300 --> 15:10.833
She kicked me
so hard in the knee.

15:10.900 --> 15:13.700
Blew up big
as a honeydew melon.

15:15.333 --> 15:17.567
Well, I wouldn't be writing
no advice columns

15:17.633 --> 15:19.133
if I were you.

15:24.400 --> 15:26.967
Don't get yourself
caught with a pig in a poke.

15:27.067 --> 15:29.400
I'm Froggy,
and here at Froggy's Hoggies,

15:29.467 --> 15:32.100
I guarantee you
the most top quality hogs

15:32.167 --> 15:34.967
for all your smoking,
roasting, broiling,

15:35.067 --> 15:36.433
and barbequing needs.

15:36.500 --> 15:38.867
We do the killin',
you do the grillin'.

15:38.933 --> 15:41.167
Come to Froggy's
off of Tadpole Street.

15:41.233 --> 15:43.200
Tell them Froggy sent you.

15:45.900 --> 15:47.500
What do you think,
Miss Keister?

15:49.067 --> 15:52.100
It's Keisker,
and it's certainly sincere.

15:52.167 --> 15:55.567
-Uh, maybe a little fast.
-Wrote it myself.

15:55.633 --> 15:57.700
Would never have guessed.

15:57.767 --> 15:59.067
Uh, take a break.

15:59.133 --> 16:00.467
Practice reading it
three times in a row,

16:00.533 --> 16:01.933
and we'll try it again.

16:06.767 --> 16:08.400
Man, oh, man,

16:08.467 --> 16:11.500
Becky just does not
get the music.

16:12.667 --> 16:14.367
And she doesn't get me.

16:17.067 --> 16:19.067
I don't blame her.

16:19.067 --> 16:21.200
Sometimes, I don't get me.

16:23.267 --> 16:25.667
I mean,
I spend all my time here,

16:25.733 --> 16:28.900
trying to keep this place
going, single-handed.

16:29.667 --> 16:31.333
And all for what?

16:31.400 --> 16:34.067
Oh, so I can record
oink-oink here?

16:35.933 --> 16:38.500
-What?

16:38.567 --> 16:40.067
It's all yours.

16:40.667 --> 16:42.067
I don't follow.

16:42.133 --> 16:44.133
Go ahead. Record Mr. Froggy.

16:45.867 --> 16:47.767
Oh.

16:47.833 --> 16:50.900
-It's Mr. Hutchins, Sam.
-Who?

16:50.967 --> 16:55.067
The WHBQ station manager?
My other boss?

16:58.467 --> 17:00.767
-Hi.
-Hi.

17:00.833 --> 17:04.467
Uh, Mr. Hutchins. Welcome to
the Memphis Recording Service.

17:04.533 --> 17:05.633
What can we do for you?

17:07.167 --> 17:08.867
Well, actually,
I'm here to see Marion.

17:08.933 --> 17:12.100
But if I've come
at an inopportune time,

17:12.167 --> 17:14.233
-I could just come back...
-Not at all.

17:18.600 --> 17:19.933
Well, then...

17:21.067 --> 17:22.533
-Oh.
-I...

17:23.633 --> 17:26.167
-I was, uh,

17:26.233 --> 17:30.100
wondering if you were
free for dinner this evening?

17:31.867 --> 17:34.333
Well, I am actually.

17:36.633 --> 17:39.233
Uh, Marion,

17:39.300 --> 17:41.667
we have a recording
session tonight.

17:41.733 --> 17:43.367
Do we?

17:43.433 --> 17:47.467
Oh, well, I'm sure
you can handle it, Sam.

17:47.533 --> 17:48.967
Single-handedly.

17:51.300 --> 17:54.200
-Let me walk you out.
-I would love that.

17:54.733 --> 17:56.067
Sam.

17:56.067 --> 17:58.567
-Was a pleasure.
-So long.

18:02.567 --> 18:05.633
Do you think I should mention
my finger-licking baby backs?

18:05.700 --> 18:07.067
They are something!

18:07.833 --> 18:09.100
Sure.

18:12.667 --> 18:15.433
Don't get yourself caught
with a pig in a poke.

18:15.500 --> 18:18.167
I'm Froggy,
and here at Froggy's Hoggies,

18:18.233 --> 18:20.567
I guarantee you
the most top quality hogs

18:20.633 --> 18:24.567
for all your smoking,
roasting, broiling, boiling,

18:24.633 --> 18:25.900
and barbequing...

18:25.967 --> 18:33.067
♪ Anytime
you're feeling lonely

18:33.133 --> 18:38.733
♪ Anytime you're feeling blue

18:40.533 --> 18:47.467
♪ Anytime
you feel down-hearted

18:47.533 --> 18:53.200
♪ That will prove your love
for me is true

18:54.633 --> 19:01.700
♪ Anytime
you're thinking 'bout me

19:01.767 --> 19:07.600
♪ That's the time
I'll think of you

19:09.167 --> 19:15.767
♪ Anytime you say
you want me back again

19:15.833 --> 19:22.467
♪ That's the time
I'll come back home to you ♪

19:28.233 --> 19:30.800
There you go.
Thank you very much.

19:33.467 --> 19:37.200
Well, I'm sorry,
sold out.

19:39.567 --> 19:41.733
Thank you.
Thank you, ma'am.

19:48.400 --> 19:50.067
Hey.

20:00.667 --> 20:04.000
Tickets? Tickets? Thanks.
Excuse me.

20:04.067 --> 20:06.533
Thank you, ma'am. Thank you.

20:06.600 --> 20:08.033
-Yes?
-Have you seen my mom?

20:08.100 --> 20:09.633
No, I have not
seen your mother.

20:09.700 --> 20:12.067
Well, she said she was going
in and I could go right in.

